<item>
            <title>[LOG4J2-964] StringFormattedMessage serialization is incorrect</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LOG4J2-964</link>
                <project id="12310790" key="LOG4J2">Log4j 2</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The method &lt;tt&gt;writeObject(final ObjectOutputStream out)&lt;/tt&gt; of the class &lt;tt&gt;org.apache.logging.log4j.message.StringFormattedMessage&lt;/tt&gt; does not write the stringArgs array into the output stream. This causes &lt;tt&gt;readObject(final ObjectInputStream in)&lt;/tt&gt; to throw an &lt;tt&gt;EOFException&lt;/tt&gt; when trying to deserialize.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There is another bug in the same method. The line &lt;tt&gt;stringArgs&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;i&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; = obj.toString();&lt;/tt&gt; throws a &lt;tt&gt;NullPointerException&lt;/tt&gt; when obj is null.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
